== Overview ==
This class is an iOS (iPhone and iPad) replacement of UILabel class that interprets Bold and Emphasis HTML tags (&lt;b&gt; and &lt;em&gt;) in the text attribute of the Label.

<ul>
<li>Parts of text without tags are rendered with '''textColor''' and '''textFont''';</li>
<li>Parts of text between &lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt; are rendered with '''highlightedTextColor''' and '''highlightedTextFont''';</li>
<li>Parts of text between &lt;em&gt;&lt;/em&gt; are rendered with '''textColor''' and '''emphasisTextFont''';</li>
<li>Parts of text between &lt;b&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/b&gt; are rendered with '''highlightedTextColor''' and '''emphasisTextFont''';</li>
</ul>

This implementation is faster than UIWebView and is perfect for '''UITableViewCell''', it is very easy to customize it for your needs.

== Example ==

<pre>
- (UITableViewCell *)tableView:(UITableView *)tableView 
         cellForRowAtIndexPath:(NSIndexPath *)indexPath 
{
    static NSString *CellIdentifier = @"CellIdentifier";
    UITableViewCell *cell = [tableView dequeueReusableCellWithIdentifier:CellIdentifier];
    if (cell == nil) {
        cell = [[UITableViewCell alloc]
                initWithStyle:UITableViewCellStyleDefault
                reuseIdentifier:CellIdentifier];
        AlgoliaUILabel *lblMainLabel = [[AlgoliaUILabel alloc] initWithFrame:CGRectMake(5, 5, 300, 45)];
        lblMainLabel.tag = 42;
        lblMainLabel.font = [UIFont fontWithName:@"Helvetica" size:20];
        lblMainLabel.highlightedTextFont = [UIFont fontWithName:@"Helvetica-Bold" size:20];
        lblMainLabel.backgroundColor = [UIColor clearColor];
        lblMainLabel.textColor = [UIColor blackColor];
        lblMainLabel.highlightedTextColor = [UIColor blackColor];
        [cell.contentView addSubview:lblMainLabel];
    }
    UILabel* label = (UILabel*)[cell viewWithTag:42];
    label.text = @"<em>Note:</em> This is a <b>highlighted</b> word";
    return cell;
}
</pre>
